
EdTech & IT Services Website

1. Project Overview

Project Name: EdTech & IT Services Website
Client Type: IT Services / EdTech Company
Designer Role: UI/UX Designer (Research, UX Strategy, UI Design, Usability)
Platform: Responsive Web (Desktop, Tablet, Mobile)

 Objective

Design a modern, scalable, and conversion-focused website that showcases the company’s IT services, expertise, portfolio, and credibility while enabling users to easily explore services and initiate projects or consultations.



 2. Problem Statement

Many IT and EdTech service websites fail due to:

. Information overload without clear hierarchy
. Poor conversion flow (CTA confusion)
. Low trust signals despite strong capabilities
. Inconsistent visual language

Design Goal: Create a clean, professional, and intuitive experience that builds trust, communicates value quickly, and drives users toward consultation and project initiation.



 3. Target Users & Personas

 Primary Users

1. Startup Founders – Looking for tech partners
2. Enterprise Clients – Seeking scalable solutions
3. EdTech Institutions – Interested in AI/ML-driven platforms
4. Product Managers – Evaluating vendors

 User Needs

. Clear understanding of services
. Proof of expertise and experience
. Easy contact & consultation booking
. Professional and modern UI



 4. User Journey

1. Landing on Homepage
   ↓
2. Understanding Company Value Proposition
   ↓
3. Exploring Services & Expertise
   ↓
4. Reviewing Portfolio & Client Feedback
   ↓
5. Trust Building (Stats, Clients, Team)
   ↓
6. Conversion (Contact / Book Consultation)



 5. Information Architecture

 Main Navigation

. Home
. Services
. Projects
. About Us
. Contact Us
. Get Started (Primary CTA)

 Footer Navigation

. Services
. Company
. Policies
. Contact Information
. Social Media



 6. Design System

 Color Palette

. Primary: Dark Blue / Indigo (Trust & Technology)
. Accent: Gradient highlights (Innovation & Energy)
. Neutral: White, Light Grey (Readability)

 Typography

. Headings: Sans-serif, Bold
. Body Text: Clean sans-serif, Regular
. CTA Text: Medium to Semi-bold

 UI Principles

. Minimal & professional
. Consistent spacing and alignment
. Strong visual hierarchy
. High contrast for accessibility



 7. Page-wise UX & UI Breakdown

 7.1 Homepage

Purpose: First impression & value communication

Key Sections:

. Hero Section with strong headline and CTA
. Company stats (Projects, AI Solutions, Support)
. Services overview
. Development process
. Portfolio highlights
. Testimonials
. Trusted clients
. Final CTA

UX Decisions:

. Clear hero message for quick understanding
. Social proof above the fold
. Repeated CTAs for conversion



 7.2 Services Section

Services Displayed:

. Blockchain Development
. Cybersecurity
. App Development
. Website Development
. AI/ML Development

UX Strategy:

. Card-based layout for scannability
. Short descriptions with "Explore with us" CTA
. Icons/visuals for quick recognition



 7.3 Development Process

Steps:

1. Discovery
2. Design
3. Development
4. Delivery

UX Goal:

. Build transparency
. Reduce user hesitation
. Show structured workflow



 7.4 Portfolio Page

Content:

. Project showcase
. Tech stack tags (AI/ML, React, Node.js)
. Performance outcomes

UX Rationale:

. Visual-first layout
. Highlights real-world impact



 7.5 Testimonials & Clients

Elements:

. Client feedback cards
. Client names & roles
. Trusted brand logos

UX Goal:

. Increase trust
. Reduce decision friction



 7.6 About Us Page

Sections:

. Company vision
. Years of experience
. Team expertise
. Core values

Core Values Highlighted:

. Innovation
. Quality
. Collaboration



 7.7 Team Section

Purpose: Humanize the brand

UX Approach:

. Role-based expertise cards
. Simple bios
. Clear professional presentation



 7.8 Contact & Lead Generation

Contact Form Fields:

. Name
. Email
. Phone
. Project details
. Services interested

UX Strategy:

. Minimal required fields
. Clear labels
. Strong CTA button



 8. Accessibility & Usability Considerations

. Adequate color contrast
. Readable font sizes
. Mobile-first responsive design
. Clear CTA buttons
. Simple form interactions



 9. Design Impact & Outcomes

. Improved clarity of services
. Stronger trust through social proof
. Better conversion flow
. Scalable layout for future growth



 10. Tools Used

. Design: Figma
. Prototyping: Figma Interactive Prototypes
. Research: Competitive analysis
. Handoff: Design system & components



 11. Future Enhancements

. Dark mode
. Micro-interactions
. AI chatbot integration
. Advanced analytics dashboard



 12. Conclusion

This UI/UX design focuses on clarity, trust, and conversion while maintaining a modern and scalable visual identity. The design effectively bridges business goals with user needs, resulting in an intuitive and professional digital experience.



Designed by: Sanskrati Agrawal
Role: UI/UX Designer
